{
  "version": "0.0.1",
  "_comment": "Every config runs the FULL game server (node server/index.mjs) — it serves the client AND the /api the client now requires, so `preview` enters the world normally. Each preview gets its OWN scratch account/world store in /tmp (isolated per port) so no two previews, or a preview and the live server, ever clobber each other's data. To work against real/live data, don't run a server here — point at api.gorkscape.ca. See COORDINATION.md.",
